---
title: Chicken Saltimbocca with Mushroom Risotto
description: The Italian word saltimbocca loosely translates as ‘jump in the mouth’. Tender chicken and savoury sage, all wrapped in serrano ham is a feast for the senses. It sits atop a porcini risotto enriched with butter and cheese. Italians call the final stage of risotto making where these are beaten in the 'mantecatura'. It makes everything extra creamy. Definitely something to make the taste buds leap for joy!
